org.eclipse.incquery.viewers.runtime.model

Class ViewerState

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.incquery.viewers.runtime.model.ViewerState
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ViewerStateList, ViewerStateSet

    public abstract class ViewerState
extends java.lang.Object

    A Viewer state represents a stateful data model for an IncQuery Viewer. The state is capable of either returning observable lists of its content, and is also capable of sending of sending state change notifications based to IViewerStateListener implementations.

    A Viewer can be initialized directly with a set of patterns and model, or a IncQueryViewerDataModel can be used to prepare and share such data between instances.

    A ViewerState needs to be cleaned up using the dispose() method to unregister all listeners.

    Author:
    Zoltan Ujhelyi, Istvan Rath
